{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"HAND-ADJUDICATION ERROR FOUND (S001) — surfaced by the corrected grounded adjudicator prototype. During adjudication I ruled S001 (ticket e165, finding 'event_append.py EVENT_TYPES not in file_impact') FP = escaped defect, claiming I had 'verified' it against code. I verified the CODE fact (event_append.py line 54 does have its own EVENT_TYPES frozenset) but did NOT read the whole plan — exactly the truncated rater's failure. e165's plan SECTION 5 'Write-path allowlist' (at char ~8166, PAST the 6000-char PLAN_CAP) already states: 'src/rebar/_store/event_append.py: KEY_ADD/KEY_REVOKE MUST be added to the hardcoded EVENT_TYPES frozenset ... or _validate_event raises a StoreError ... Separate from the reducer known-type set in _version.py — BOTH must be updated.' So the plan already covers the substance; the finding is a restatement absent only from the file_impact ARRAY, not an escaped defect. The grounded verifier (whole plan + real code grep) scored it validity 0.375 -> correctly dropped. Concrete proof the human layer was contaminated by the same 'didn't see the whole plan' failure — reinforces the full rebuild."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784236391297298001,"uuid":"b02a46fd-901f-4cd4-ae04-d8f223cd8e89"}